<h2>
Research <span>Overview</span>
</h2>

<p>
Disease epigenomics examines how epigenetic regulation changes during disease initiation, progression, adaptation, and treatment response. Unlike DNA sequence mutations, epigenomic changes can dynamically regulate gene activity without altering the underlying genome sequence.
</p>

<p>
At PanorOmics, disease epigenomics is presented as a core epigenomics research area: a bridge between genome regulation, cancer biology, aging, immune regulation, biomarker discovery, therapeutic resistance, and precision medicine.
</p>

